article.description: — Chris Ledlum's 30 points led Harvard past Loyola Chicago 61-55 on Friday.
article.headline: Ledlum scores 30, Harvard takes down Loyola Chicago 61-55
article.linkText: Ledlum scores 30, Harvard takes down Loyola Chicago 61-55
article.story: BOSTON -- — Chris Ledlum's 30 points led Harvard past Loyola Chicago 61-55 on Friday. Ledlum also added nine rebounds and five steals for the Crimson (5-1). Chisom Okpara added eight points and Idan Tretout finished with seven points. Tom Welch led the way for the Ramblers (2-4) with 12 points. Loyola Chicago also got nine points from Ben Schwieger and eight from Bryce Golden. Harvard went into the half leading Loyola Chicago 33-26. Ledlum scored 14 points in the half. Ledlum's 16-point second half helped Harvard finish off the six-point victory. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
